The '''Figg conglomerate''',<ref name="Galactic Gazetteer">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20040325web|text=Galactic Gazetteer: Hoth and the Greater Javin|int=Galactic Gazetteer: Hoth and the Greater Javin}}</ref> also referred to as the '''Figg empire''',<ref name="Rough and Tundra">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20040325adv|text=Rough and Tundra|int=Rough and Tundra}}</ref> consisted of the multiple business ventures of the [[Figg family]], led by [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] explorer [[Ecclessis Figg/Legends|Ecclessis Figg]]. The conglomerate consisted of the [[Outer Javin Company]], [[Figg & Associates]], and [[Figg Excavations/Legends|Figg Excavations]].<ref name="Galactic Gazetteer" />

While Ecclessis Figg had dreamed for years during his youth of blazing [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperroutes]] through the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]], his dream did not become a reality until he saved the life of [[Yarith Figg|Yarith]], an Alderaanian noble traveling aboard a [[Luxury liner/Legends|luxury liner]] on the [[Corellian Trade Spine/Legends|Corellian Trade Spine]]. The couple soon married, and Yarith poured her wealth into Ecclessis's first business, the Outer Javin Company.<ref name="Galactic Gazetteer" />

Years later, Figg & Associates and Figg Excavations were founded, and the conglomerate eventually passed into the hands of the Figg family descendants. The family still maintained its holdings over the conglomerate during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="Galactic Gazetteer" />

